                                abbot <term type="ignore">Sarvajñādeva</term> was among the “one
                                hundred” paṇḍitas invited by Trisong Detsen (r. 755–797/800) to
                                assist with the translation of the Buddhist scriptures into Tibetan.
                                    <term type="ignore">Sarvajñādeva</term> assisted in the
                                translation of more than twenty-three works, including numerous
