                                may have continued into the reign of Ralpachen, who ascended the
                                throne in 815 and died in 838 or 841 <hi rend="small-caps">ce</hi>.</term>-->
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss type="place" xml:id="UT22084-063-006-38">
                            <term type="translationMain">Brahmā realms</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="sourceUnspecified">brahmāloka</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="attestedSource" n="1">tshangs pa’i ’jig rten</term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" type="attestedSource" n="1">ཚངས་པའི་འཇིག་རྟེན།</term>
                            <note type="definition">
                                <p>The heaven of Brahmā, usually located just above
                                the desire realm (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">kāmadhātu</foreign>) as one of the first levels of the form
                                realm (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">rūpadhātu</foreign>)
                                and equated with the state that one achieves in the first meditative
                                absorption (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">dhyāna</foreign>).</p>
                            </note>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss type="place" xml:id="UT22084-063-006-39">
                            <term type="translationMain">Jambudvīpa</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="sourceUnspecified">jambudvīpa</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="attestedSource" n="1">’dzam bu’i gling</term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" type="attestedSource" n="1">འཛམ་བུའི་གླིང་།</term>
                            <note type="definition" rend="override">
                                <p>The continent (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">dvīpa</foreign>) on which we live, shaped like a
                                rose apple (<foreign xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="term">jambū</foreign>)
                                according to ancient South Asian cosmology.</p>
                            </note>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss type="place" xml:id="UT22084-063-006-40">
                            <term type="translationMain">Jeta’s Grove</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="sourceUnspecified">jetavana</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="attestedSource" n="1">rgyal bu rgyal byed kyi tshal</term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" type="attestedSource" n="1">རྒྱལ་བུ་རྒྱལ་བྱེད་ཀྱི་ཚལ།</term>
                            <note type="definition">
                                <p>See “Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍada’s Park.”</p>
                            </note>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss type="place" xml:id="UT22084-063-006-84">
                            <term type="translationMain">Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍada’s Park</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="attestedOther" status="verified">jetavanam anāthapiṇḍadasyārāmaḥ</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="attestedSource" n="1">rgyal bu rgyal byed kyi tshal mgon med zas sbyin gyi kun dga’ ra ba</term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" type="attestedSource" n="1">རྒྱལ་བུ་རྒྱལ་བྱེད་ཀྱི་ཚལ་མགོན་མེད་ཟས་སྦྱིན་གྱི་ཀུན་དགའ་ར་བ།</term>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss xml:id="UT22084-063-006-41" type="place" mode="match">
                            <term type="translationMain">Mount Sumeru</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="sourceUnspecified">sumeru</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="attestedSource" n="1">ri rab</term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" type="attestedSource" n="1">རི་རབ།</term>
                            <note type="definition" rend="override">
                                <p>The great mountain at the center of the universe according to ancient Indian cosmology.</p>
                            </note>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <gloss type="place" xml:id="UT22084-063-006-42">
                            <term type="translationMain">Śrāvastī</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Sa-Ltn" type="sourceUnspecified">śrāvastī</term>
                            <term xml:lang="Bo-Ltn" type="attestedSource" n="1">mnyan yod</term>
                            <term xml:lang="bo" type="attestedSource" n="1">མཉན་ཡོད།</term>
                            <note type="definition" rend="override">
                                <p>During the life of the Buddha, <term rend="ignore">Śrāvastī</term> was a major city in the kingdom of
                                Kosala, in present day Uttar Pradesh.</p>
                            </note>
                        </gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
